OL,3,CBlackpool man jailed over 'audacious'
OL,4,C#1k train ticket con
OL,6,FA man has been jailed after he
OL,7,Fswindled a rail company out of more
OL,8,Fthan #1,000 by dishonestly using a
OL,9,Fcompensation scheme.
OL,11,FThomas Ingram, 38, of Cheltenham Road,
OL,12,FBlackpool, was jailed for 16 months at
OL,13,FPreston Crown Court after he pleaded
OL,14,Fguilty to fraud by false
OL,15,Frepresentation.
OL,17,FIn total Ingram submitted 28 claims
OL,18,Fbetween 23 November 2020 and 26
OL,19,FJanuary 2023 to the value of #5,372.
