OL,3,CBlackpool man jailed over 'audacious'
OL,4,C#1k train ticket con
OL,6,FTransport for Wales had paid out
OL,7,F#1,294 with the other claims being
OL,8,Frejected due to suspicions about their
OL,9,Flegitimacy.
OL,11,FInvestigating officer DC Callum
OL,12,FLancaster said: "Ingram was audacious
OL,13,Fand brazen in his numerous attempts to
OL,14,Fdefraud railway companies.
OL,16,F"Despite a common misconception,
OL,17,Fticket fraud is by no means a
OL,18,Fvictimless crime, the costs incurred
OL,19,Fto the companies are reflected in
OL,20,Fprice increases and a delay in
OL,21,Fcompensating genuine claimants.
